Brazilian Stock Movers: Brasil Foods, Tam, Tim Participacoes

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-07-08T16:56:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-08/brazilian-stock-movers-brasil-foods-tam-tim-participacoes.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:31 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa index declined 1.3 percent to 61,412.12.  BRF  Brasil Foods  SA (BRFS3) dropped 2.5 percent to 24.96
reais. The world’s biggest poultry exporter still hasn’t
concluded talks with  Brazil ’s antitrust regulator for its
acquisition of Sadia SA, said Olavo Chinaglia, a member of the
agency known as Cade. The antitrust agency will likely meet with
representatives of Brasil Foods at least once more before it
rules on the acquisition on July 13, he said.  Tam SA (TAMM4)  (TAMM4 BS), the airline being acquired by Lan
Airlines SA, declined 2.9 percent to 35.79 reais. Chile’s
antitrust tribunal president Tomas Menchaca told newspaper La
Tercera that a ruling on the planned takeover probably won’t be
delivered until August. The court, known as TDLC, previously
estimated the outcome of its investigation would be made known
by the end of this month.  Tim Participacoes SA (TCSL4)  (TCSL4 BS) gained 1.9 percent to 7.58
reais. The Brazilian unit of  Italy ’s largest phone company will
buy AES Atimus Group for about 700 million euros ($1 billion)
from Companhia Brasiliana de Energia to add network capacity in
Sao Paulo and  Rio de Janeiro , its parent said today in a
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in Sao Paulo at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  